                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            The dating of the manuscript hinges on the date provided by
                            <ref target="#coloph1">the colophon</ref>, interpreted as 
                            <origDate notBefore="1443" notAfter="1444" evidence="internal-date" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">1443/44</origDate>
                            by Strelcyn 
                            or 
                            <origDate notBefore="1459" notAfter="1460" resp="PRS9619Uhlig" evidence="internal-date">1459/60</origDate>
                            by Uhlig (see the description of <ref target="#coloph1">the colophon</ref>).
                         Strelcyn offers two possible interpretations 
                            of the <ref target="#coloph1">the colophon</ref>: the manuscript might have originally contained
                          a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Gadla Mikāʾel</foreign>
                            and a <foreign xml:lang="gez">Gadla Māryām</foreign> which preceded the
                            works described here; alternatively,
                            <foreign xml:lang="gez">Gadla Mikāʾel</foreign> might refer
                            to <ref target="#ms_i5"/> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">Gadla Māryām</foreign> to 
                            <ref target="#ms_i4"/>.
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>Acquired by Conti Rossini in November 
                            <date when="1937">1937</date> from the church of
                            <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1193AddiQw">ʿĀddi Qʷanṣi</placeName> in 
                            <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3764Hamase">Ḥamāsen</placeName>
                            (see <ref target="#e1"/>).</provenance>
                    </history>
                    
